Senior Investment Strategy Engineer/Officer

At VicRoads we work to make a more thriving and liveable Victoria, providing Victorians with safe and easy connections to the people and places that matter most to them. About The Team

The Transport Vehicular Movement team in Metro South East plays an important role in identifying network capacity issues on the arterial road network and establishing the strategic importance for capacity improvement works at key locations, including growth areas. The team collaborates with a number of internal and external stakeholders to better understand and address issues of concern to road users, and is responsible for prioritising project proposals for funding, which are considered under various Government programs and/or other funding sources.

Working as part of the Transport Vehicular Movement team and reporting to the Team Leader, this is a full-time ongoing role. Please note that this position could also be structured as a part-time or job share arrangement. Do not hesitate to contact us if this is something you want like to discuss.

  • Excellent verbal and written communication skills;
  • Confidence with stakeholder and customer engagement;
  • Ability to apply project management principles in managing activities;
  • Ability to perform efficiently under pressure; and
  • A tertiary qualification in Engineering or related discipline.
We Are Looking For a Person Who

About the Ideal Candidate
  • Has a tertiary qualification in Engineering/Planning or a related discipline
  • Values being part of a team with a variety of experience;
  • Can prioritise to handle a variety of important issues;
  • Has a passion learning new things and develop their capabilities;
  • Has a wide and varied knowledge of the transport system; and
  • Can work both in the 'big picture' and in the detail.
To attract, retain and develop talented people, we provide genuine flexibility, a culture that supports people to be their best and on top of that - great opportunities for career development. We embrace diversity and inclusion and are proud our workforce reflects the community we serve.

KA 3.


Develop and maintain strong working relationship with key external stakeholders, including whole of government agency and departmental partners, Councils, transport user groups, and community groups to understand transport issues and ensure appropriate consultation on project proposals.

KA 4.


Maintain strong working relationships and knowledge sharing with internal stakeholders to ensure alignment with broader transport planning objectives, while considering funding and delivery challenges.

KA 5.


Use conceptual and analytical skills to prioritise and identify lists of pipeline projects which are in line with government transport and planning objectives.

KA 6.


Coach, motivate and develop less experience team members and ensure an appropriate standard of work is maintained.

Ability to exercise professional independent judgement to effectively identify, build and maintain stakeholder relations with various government departments and industry representatives to achieve successful project outcomes.

KC 4.

KC 5.


Demonstrated knowledge in transport and asset management priorities and programs under project based supervision incorporating government strategies, and key stakeholder requirements.

Ability to create an environment where accountability, teamwork, customer focus and innovation are a focus of the team.
